00:43:49.293 --> 00:43:52.396
Then it's like.
"Fuck. Hannah snaked twice. Fine."

916
00:43:55.232 --> 00:43:56.634
-[Keenan] Hey.
-[Kassy] Hello.

917
00:43:56.700 --> 00:43:58.502
-[Keenan] How are you doing?
-[Kassy] Good.

918
00:43:58.569 --> 00:44:00.404
[narrator] <i>Keenan's still mad at Kassy.</i>

919
00:44:00.471 --> 00:44:03.040
<i>I haven't seen a game
cause this much trouble</i>

920
00:44:03.107 --> 00:44:07.645
<i>since Granny Stirling put her hip out
playing Twister last Christmas.</i>

921
00:44:08.145 --> 00:44:11.315
I want to talk to you because I could tell
you were annoyed by the game.

922
00:44:11.382 --> 00:44:13.917
Yeah. I was feeling
some type of way. goddamn.

923
00:44:13.984 --> 00:44:15.819
[Kassy]
But I want you to hear me out first.

924
00:44:15.886 --> 00:44:18.188
-[Keenan] No. for sure...
-Last time. I heard you out. so...

925
00:44:18.255 --> 00:44:20.491
[Keenan] You know I'm always
gonna listen. Always. For sure.

926
00:44:20.557 --> 00:44:21.925
-[Kassy] I hope so.
-You got it.

927
00:44:21.992 --> 00:44:22.993
[Kassy] Um.

928
00:44:24.261 --> 00:44:28.732
So. I wasn't thinking.
And it wasn't like I was wrong.

929
00:44:28.799 --> 00:44:30.367
It was like. we do look at each other.

930
00:44:30.434 --> 00:44:32.202
So I don't think
I was saying anything wrong.

931
00:44:32.269 --> 00:44:33.971
But at the same time. it's a challenge.

932
00:44:34.038 --> 00:44:37.174
I didn't mean anything serious.

933
00:44:37.241 --> 00:44:39.443
The comment that you made.

934
00:44:39.510 --> 00:44:42.479
the "giving me googly eyes
while I'm in a couple."

935
00:44:42.546 --> 00:44:45.282
-that's more disrespectful than anything.
-But weren't you looking at me?

936
00:44:45.349 --> 00:44:47.451
"Looking at me"
and "giving me googly eyes"...

937
00:44:47.518 --> 00:44:49.720
"We exchanged looks."
I wouldn't have got mad at that.

938
00:44:49.787 --> 00:44:50.854
"Give me googly eyes"...

939
00:44:50.921 --> 00:44:53.257
But you were looking at me
and smiling. right?

940
00:44:53.323 --> 00:44:54.958
What do you mean?

941
00:44:55.025 --> 00:44:57.061
You'd be looking away.
There were moments where...

942
00:44:57.127 --> 00:44:58.962
And that's after
I catch you staring at me.

943
00:44:59.029 --> 00:45:00.998
No. I look up.
and you'll be staring at me too.

944
00:45:01.065 --> 00:45:02.566
Come on. Kass.

945
00:45:02.633 --> 00:45:04.935
Kass. I'm not denying that
we haven't looked at each other.

946
00:45:05.002 --> 00:45:06.236
-I never denied that.
-Exactly.

947
00:45:06.303 --> 00:45:07.971
But I wasn't going deep into it.

948
00:45:08.038 --> 00:45:10.174
[Keenan] Every time I try
to get into trying to explain

949
00:45:10.240 --> 00:45:12.176
how it makes me feel. this.
that and the third.

950
00:45:12.242 --> 00:45:15.079
you quickly counter with.
"But that's not what I meant."

951
00:45:15.145 --> 00:45:17.614
And honestly. I'm irritated.

952
00:45:19.516 --> 00:45:22.853
If you agree with it.
if you understand it. that's up to you.

953
00:45:22.920 --> 00:45:24.822
I'm just trying to elaborate
on how I felt.

954
00:45:24.888 --> 00:45:26.890
But every time I get started.
you cut me off.

955
00:45:26.957 --> 00:45:29.126
So are you ready
for me to elaborate to you?

956
00:45:29.693 --> 00:45:31.562
The reason why I took it so personal

957
00:45:31.628 --> 00:45:35.199
is because I never denied the fact
that I ever looked at you

958
00:45:35.265 --> 00:45:37.101
or make eye contact with you.

959
00:45:37.167 --> 00:45:41.305
But the comment of googly eyes.
how I perceived it is.

960
00:45:41.371 --> 00:45:43.540
"I'm in a couple.
but I'm fawning over somebody else."

961
00:45:43.607 --> 00:45:44.908
That's just how I perceive it.

962
00:45:44.975 --> 00:45:47.845
It was the wrong comment. I felt stupid.

963
00:45:48.579 --> 00:45:53.016
I feel like I keep giving a little bit.
giving a little bit.

964
00:45:53.083 --> 00:45:55.185
and then I get publicly embarrassed.

965
00:45:56.587 --> 00:45:58.255
I ain't gonna keep
getting embarrassed. man.

966
00:45:58.322 --> 00:45:59.690
It is what it is.

967
00:46:14.905 --> 00:46:17.274
{\an8}[narrator]
<i>Welcome back to</i> Love Island USA.

968
00:46:17.341 --> 00:46:20.878
<i>Oh. Bergie's only been coupled up
with Kassy for one day.</i>

969
00:46:20.944 --> 00:46:25.182
<i>but already he wants to tell her
those magical three little words...</i>

970
00:46:25.783 --> 00:46:28.252
<i>"I fancy Carmen."</i>

971
00:46:28.318 --> 00:46:31.588
[Bergie] I felt good about it. obviously.
because I had an interest in Carmen.

972
00:46:31.655 --> 00:46:33.457
-[Kassy] Yeah.
-[Bergie] I won't lie about it...

973
00:46:33.524 --> 00:46:36.293
I wish you didn't have to
talk about how excited you were.

974
00:46:36.360 --> 00:46:39.296
We should talk about us first. you know?

975
00:46:39.363 --> 00:46:42.466
It made me just feel insecure in a way.

976
00:46:42.533 --> 00:46:45.068
-[Bergie] Yeah. Sorry.
-You know?

977
00:46:45.702 --> 00:46:47.371
It's something I have to work on. but...

978
00:46:47.437 --> 00:46:51.074
Yeah. I know it's new.
I know you haven't dated before.

979
00:46:51.141 --> 00:46:54.178
It was kind of a punch in the face.

980
00:46:54.244 --> 00:46:56.213
I was like. "What about our kiss."
you know? Just...

981
00:46:56.280 --> 00:46:58.115
-[Bergie] Sorry.
-It's okay.

982
00:46:58.182 --> 00:47:00.250
I just wanted to say that.

983
00:47:00.317 --> 00:47:02.820
But at the same time.
I know it's still fresh.

984
00:47:02.886 --> 00:47:04.421
and you've talked to Carmen more.

985
00:47:04.488 --> 00:47:05.923
and so you guys probably...

986
00:47:05.989 --> 00:47:08.725
Actually. I don't think I've talked
to Carmen more than us.

987
00:47:08.792 --> 00:47:11.128
-I think we've had...
-[Kassy] What attracts you more to Carmen?

988
00:47:11.195 --> 00:47:12.462
If you don't mind me asking.

989
00:47:12.529 --> 00:47:14.298
Just some of the personal values.

990
00:47:14.364 --> 00:47:16.533
She does want to move back to Wisconsin.

991
00:47:16.600 --> 00:47:19.970
she said. maybe potentially in her 30s
and start a family there.

992
00:47:20.037 --> 00:47:21.405
which is right next to Minnesota.

993
00:47:21.471 --> 00:47:23.707
Oh. okay. So. it's just closer to you.

994
00:47:23.774 --> 00:47:25.742
And you've stated you only want two kids.

995
00:47:25.809 --> 00:47:28.812
but with Carmen. she wants four.
and that's kind of what I want too.

996
00:47:28.879 --> 00:47:30.981
-[Kassy] Okay.
-So. I'm just looking long-term too.

997
00:47:31.682 --> 00:47:34.251
I feel like she showed
physical interest in me.

998
00:47:34.318 --> 00:47:36.019
-[Kassy] Yeah.
-And especially today.

999
00:47:36.086 --> 00:47:37.554
She went way out of her comfort zone.

1000
00:47:37.621 --> 00:47:40.657
[Bergie] Pretty much sacrificed her
whole relationship with Victor today

1001
00:47:40.724 --> 00:47:42.693
to show interest in me.

1002
00:47:42.759 --> 00:47:46.363
which really sucks for Victor.
but it shows me a lot.

1003
00:47:46.430 --> 00:47:47.731
Yeah.

1004
00:47:47.798 --> 00:47:49.833
So. tonight. probably not going to cuddle.

1005
00:47:49.900 --> 00:47:51.401
I understand.

1006
00:47:53.337 --> 00:47:54.771
[Islanders chattering]

1007
00:47:54.838 --> 00:47:56.573
-He's so unhappy.
-[Leonardo] Hear me out.

1008
00:48:01.578 --> 00:48:03.714
Do you wanna go talk
or do you not want to talk tonight?

1009
00:48:03.780 --> 00:48:05.415
-[Victor] Sure.
-Yeah. Where should we go?

1010
00:48:05.482 --> 00:48:07.284
-[Victor] I don't know.
-Let's go over here.

1011
00:48:10.053 --> 00:48:13.690
[Carmen] I'm sorry vibes are a little low.
I feel like you're definitely not...

1012
00:48:15.259 --> 00:48:17.361
-[Victor] What?
-...happy at least. you know?

1013
00:48:17.427 --> 00:48:18.996
[Victor] At least you have good eyes.

1014
00:48:19.062 --> 00:48:21.331
-[Carmen] What was that?
-At least you have good eyes.

1015
00:48:21.398 --> 00:48:23.734
[Carmen] I'm not gonna go in this talk
with negativity.

1016
00:48:23.800 --> 00:48:26.470
And if you're going to come at me with it.
we don't need to have it.

1017
00:48:26.536 --> 00:48:28.572
-So let's take a deep breath. okay?
-[Victor] My bad.

1018
00:48:30.207 --> 00:48:31.375
[Carmen] I'll sit here.

1019
00:48:34.077 --> 00:48:35.078
[Carmen] So...

1020
00:48:36.480 --> 00:48:38.649
What's got you really upset right now?

1021
00:48:38.715 --> 00:48:41.418
Because I feel like you're heated still.

1022
00:48:44.021 --> 00:48:45.656
I'm just a little confused.

1023
00:48:45.722 --> 00:48:47.958
You knew I was open
to getting to know Bergie too.

1024
00:48:48.025 --> 00:48:49.126
you know what I mean?

1025
00:48:49.192 --> 00:48:51.795
Your reaction... I thought if anything.
you were going to be like.

1026
00:48:51.862 --> 00:48:54.264
"Yeah. It's a challenge. It's a game."

1027
00:48:54.331 --> 00:48:57.334
-How?
-It wasn't serious. like...

1028
00:48:58.535 --> 00:49:02.472
You know I'm open. and so...
Like. you were pissed.

1029
00:49:02.539 --> 00:49:04.374
-[Victor] Yeah.
-Why?

1030
00:49:04.441 --> 00:49:06.009
-[Victor] Like...
-What surprised you?

1031
00:49:06.076 --> 00:49:08.478
Because you knew
I'm getting to know Bergie too.

1032
00:49:08.545 --> 00:49:11.848
Not even the only one
after the first recoupling ceremony

1033
00:49:11.915 --> 00:49:13.617
where you are the last one.

1034
00:49:13.684 --> 00:49:16.987
All the other girls
has choose their own couples

1035
00:49:17.054 --> 00:49:19.823
because that's the moment when you should

1036
00:49:19.890 --> 00:49:22.993
try to create a deeper bond
with the person that you have coupled up.

1037
00:49:23.060 --> 00:49:25.329
It's not for you to tell me
what I should have done.

1038
00:49:25.395 --> 00:49:26.930
You can talk with Bergie whenever.

1039
00:49:26.997 --> 00:49:30.000
Why is it up to you to dictate
how I get to know him?

1040
00:49:30.067 --> 00:49:31.835
I don't give a fuck about you and Bergie.

1041
00:49:31.902 --> 00:49:33.837
Because I know

1042
00:49:35.005 --> 00:49:37.941
he's no competition for me. for us.
I know that.

1043
00:49:38.008 --> 00:49:40.177
I feel like everyone thinks
the Bergie thing is...

1044
00:49:40.978 --> 00:49:42.179
No one takes it seriously.

1045
00:49:42.245 --> 00:49:44.414
But him and I grew up in the same place.

1046
00:49:44.481 --> 00:49:46.350
We connect on that. You know what I mean?

1047
00:49:56.026 --> 00:49:58.061
[Victor] I haven't made any move.

1048
00:49:58.128 --> 00:50:00.530
Anything that could make you
feel uncomfortable.

1049
00:50:00.597 --> 00:50:02.232
And I'm cool with that.

1050
00:50:03.033 --> 00:50:04.468
But Bergie gets the fun stuff.

1051
00:50:05.435 --> 00:50:07.337
And I have to see Bergie kissing you.

1052
00:50:07.404 --> 00:50:09.706
How do you think I will feel?

1053
00:50:10.207 --> 00:50:12.809
You said you were okay with it.
and clearly. you're not.

1054
00:50:15.012 --> 00:50:17.748
If you want more.
and I'm not giving you enough.

1055
00:50:17.814 --> 00:50:20.083
then maybe we're not compatible that way.

1056
00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:24.388
And I'm not used to go from more to less.

1057
00:50:24.454 --> 00:50:26.690
I don't owe you
any more loyalty than Bergie.

1058
00:50:26.757 --> 00:50:28.291
and I'm not going to apologize

1059
00:50:28.358 --> 00:50:31.094
that I took the opportunity
to get to know him.

1060
00:50:31.161 --> 00:50:34.197
I guess I just kind of feel like...
I just kind of feel disrespected.

1061
00:50:34.264 --> 00:50:36.099
I just feel like
we're not on the same page.

1062
00:50:37.768 --> 00:50:39.069
I am going to take a step back.

1063
00:50:39.136 --> 00:50:41.104
What will that mean. "a step back"?

1064
00:50:42.973 --> 00:50:45.809
I'm not. maybe.
as invested as I was yesterday.

1065
00:50:54.151 --> 00:50:56.420
Yeah. I'm going to
go check in with my girls

1066
00:50:56.486 --> 00:50:58.121
and then we can talk again later.

1067
00:50:58.188 --> 00:50:59.189
Okay.

1068
00:50:59.256 --> 00:51:02.125
-Thank you for coming and talking.
-[Victor] You're welcome. Thank you.

1069
00:51:09.032 --> 00:51:13.303
I thought we were in the same page
as to personal values.

1070
00:51:13.370 --> 00:51:14.871
and clearly. we are not.

1071
00:51:16.006 --> 00:51:17.507
[Victor] She's a really good player.

1072
00:51:18.442 --> 00:51:20.377
And she doesn't even give a single fuck.

1073
00:51:25.348 --> 00:51:27.284
[narrator] <i>Next time</i>...

1074
00:51:28.351 --> 00:51:29.886
[echoing] <i>two Islanders</i>...

1075
00:51:30.587 --> 00:51:32.456
During the challenge. I was like.

1076
00:51:32.522 --> 00:51:35.625
"I'm most comfortable with Bergie.
and I want to pick Bergie."

1077
00:51:35.692 --> 00:51:37.627
[narrator] ...<i>are getting closer.</i>

1078
00:51:37.694 --> 00:51:40.263
You literally made my heart
drop the first time I saw you.

1079
00:51:40.330 --> 00:51:42.132
I was like. "Holy shit."

1080
00:51:42.766 --> 00:51:47.304
[narrator] <i>And a very special bombshell</i>

1081
00:51:49.005 --> 00:51:50.340
<i>hits the villa.</i>

1082
00:51:52.676 --> 00:51:55.579
{\an8}Vanderpump Rules' <i>Ariana Madix</i>...

1083
00:51:57.914 --> 00:52:00.150
{\an8}<i>delivers the drama.</i>

